cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finite automata and their properties.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper presents open problems related to combinatorics and graph theory.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the logical properties of automata.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of constructing completely reachable automata.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the properties of input words that can generate completely reachable automata.
